Key Match Events: Qatar won the match 3-0, ending India's 15-match unbeaten streak at home.
Yusuf Abdurisag scored the final goal for Qatar in the 86th minute.
Sandesh Jhingan made crucial saves, including one in the 57th minute and another in the 32nd minute.
Pre-Game Insights: Qatar coach Carlos Queiroz expressed excitement about the match and the challenge of playing in India.
India coach Igor Stimac emphasized the importance of giving their best performance and urged the team to play all out.
Post-Match Reflections: India's loss ended their 15-match unbeaten run at home.
Qatar demonstrated their dominance and control throughout the match.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was played at the Kalinga Stadium in Bhubaneswar.
The game was part of the FIFA World Cup 2026 AFC qualifiers.
